						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in the Mahārajasvāmin (Vishṇu) temple.</p>						

						<p>Circa 14th century.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record registers gifts of lands. The extant portion of the date refers to <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1 • • •,</hi> all other details of date, king, etc. being lost. It refers to a <hi rend="italic">nāyaka.</hi> </p>						

